# AlpacaLive — Cursor AI Rules

## Project
Open-source PWA oncology diary. React 19 + TypeScript + Vite + Tailwind + Dexie (IndexedDB).

## CRITICAL RULES — NEVER BREAK

1. MEDICAL DATA = JSON ONLY
   - All medical facts live in `medical-knowledge/` as .json files
   - App imports via `src/lib/medical-data/knowledge-registry.ts`
   - NEVER hardcode drug names, norms, interactions, or side effects in .ts/.tsx files
   - To add medical data → edit JSON in medical-knowledge/, NOT TypeScript

2. PATIENT DATA = LOCAL ONLY
   - IndexedDB via Dexie — data never leaves device
   - PII sanitizer strips personal data before any AI API call
   - NEVER add analytics, tracking, external data collection, or server-side storage

3. AI = EXPLAIN ONLY, NEVER SUGGEST
   - System prompt (`src/lib/system-prompt.ts`) has absolute bans
   - AI must NEVER say "you should take", "I recommend", "stop taking"
   - Every analysis needs disclaimer
   - NEVER weaken system prompt constraints or input-guard.ts patterns

4. SECURITY LAYERS
   - `src/lib/input-guard.ts` — prompt injection detection (20+ patterns), file validation, rate limiting
   - Data extraction whitelist — only whitelisted fields written to DB
   - NEVER remove security patterns or bypass validation

5. DEMO = SEPARATE DATABASE
   - Real data: AlpacaLiveDB (never touched by demo)
   - Demo data: AlpacaLiveDemoDB (separate IndexedDB)
   - Switch in `src/lib/db.ts`

## Stack
React 19, TypeScript 6, Vite 8, Tailwind CSS 4, Dexie.js, Vitest (327 tests)

## File Structure
- Components: `src/components/<feature>/<Name>.tsx`
- Logic: `src/lib/<module>.ts`
- Medical data: `medical-knowledge/<category>/<file>.json`
- Tests: `src/__tests__/<module>.test.ts`
- Types: `src/types/index.ts`
- Translations: `src/lib/translations/{pl,en}.ts`

## Before Committing
- `npx tsc --noEmit` — 0 errors
- `npm test` — all tests pass
- `npm run build` — succeeds
- New DB fields → add to `input-guard.ts` ALLOWED_FIELDS

## Commit Format
```
Type: description (#issue)
Types: Feat, Fix, Medical, Docs, Style, Refactor, Test, Chore, Security, Legal
```

## Do NOT
- Add console.log to production code
- Add npm dependencies without justification
- Modify medical-knowledge/ structure without updating knowledge-registry.ts
- Create files outside established directory structure
- Add scope beyond what was asked
- Weaken any security or privacy mechanism
